This directory (Glue_Ercolessi_Adams_Al) contains an EAM Model created by
Ercolessi and Adams (for aluminum) written in F90 and based on the pair
functional template in DOCs/TEMPLATEs/.

Reference: F. Ercolessi and J. B. Adams, "Interatomic Potentials from 
First-Principles Calculations: the Force-Matching Method",
Europhys. Lett., 26:583-588 (1994).

The contents of the directory are as follows (before any compilation if performed):

LICENSE.CDDL
     The Common Development and Distribution License (CDDL) Version 1.0 file

Makefile
     Makefile to compile and build executables with GNU or Intel compilers

README
     This file

Glue_Ercolessi_Adams_Al.F90
     Fortran module file that contains the implementation of the Ercolessi and
     Adams EAM Model

Glue_Ercolessi_Adams_Al.kim
     KIM descriptor file, contains all variables and methods that are exposed
     through the KIM API interface
